</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Small C2 accumulator O-ring (6)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
– Above two O-rings are same.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
21.8 mm (0.86 in.)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
2.6 mm (0.10 in.)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new O-rings to each accumulator piston and apply A/T fluid to them.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Make sure that O-rings are not twisted or caught when installing.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install B1, C1, C2 accumulator pistons and springs by referring to the following table.
</ptxt>
<spec>
